cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the security and privacy threats in vehicular networks and proposes a permissioned blockchain solution for resource sharing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses consensus mechanisms and incentive mechanisms, which are relevant to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a smart contract design, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
